 <!-- Introduction -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of the data that identify experience and the association of 
     experience with a person or an organization. Experience can be defined
     as knowledge or skill acquired over time through practical contact with
     and observation of facts or events. Typical examples of experience are:
     years served, hours flown,  miles driven.
   </p>
 </purpose>

